  "body": "I've been pulling my hair out trying get kubectl talk to my local cluster.\nIt seems that kubectl merges the local `.kubeconfig` file with values pulled down from the cloud.\n\nI've done the following:\n\n```\nexport KUBERNETES_PROVIDER=local\nkubectl=_output/local/bin/darwin/amd64/kubectl\n$kubectl --kubeconfig=.kubeconfig config use-context local\n# Cat local file and see that the change had effect\n$kubectl --kubeconfig=.kubeconfig config view | grep current-context\ncurrent-context: e2e-test-etune\n```\n\nThe `current-context` I just set is silently overridden.\n\nQuestions:\n- is this documented anywhere?\n- should kubectl merge in my GCE cluster when I set my cloud-provider to something else?\n- should kubectl override my previously set current-context?\n",
